ciscoTrustSecIfMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-lan-switch-snmp@cisco.com
ciscoTrustSecIfMIB.description: This MIB module defines management objects for configuration and monitoring of the interfaces in Cisco Trusted Security environment. Glossary: ACS - Cisco Secure Access Control Server IFC - TrustSec Interface Controller MACSec - Media Access Control (MAC) Security PMK - Pairwise Master Key SAP - Security Association Protocol SGT - Security Group Tag. A tag identifying its source, assigned to a packet on ingress to a TrustSec cloud, and used to determine security and other policy to be applied to it along its path through the cloud. TrustSec - Cisco Trusted Security

CtsiCasheDataSource.name: CtsiCasheDataSource
CtsiCasheDataSource.description: The source of cached authorization data. unknown - cache source type not covered by any of the follow enumerations. acs - authorization data is loaded from ACS dram - authorization data is loaded from DRAM. nvram - authorization data is loaded from NVRAM. dramOrNvram - authorization data is loaded from DRAM or NVRAM.

CtsSapNegMode.name: CtsSapNegMode
CtsSapNegMode.description: The SAP negotiation modes supported in TrustSec system. encapNoAuthenNoEncrypt - Encapsulation present, no authentication, no encryption. gcmAuthenNoEncrypt - GCM authentication, no encryption. gcmAuthenGcmEncrypt - GCM authentication, GCM encryption. noEncap - No encapsulation.

CtsSapNegModeList.name: CtsSapNegModeList
CtsSapNegModeList.description: The list of SAP negotiation modes provided within TrustSec (Cisco Trusted Security) system. Each octet represents a SAP negotiation mode which is defined in CtsSapNegMode. The DESCRIPTION clause of CtsSapNegModeList objects must fully describe the relationship between modes.

CtsiInterfaceControllerState.name: CtsiInterfaceControllerState
CtsiInterfaceControllerState.description: The state of the TrustSec Interface Controller state machine. unknown - none of the following states. initializing - the TrustSec interface controller state machine enter the initialize state when TrustSec is enabled on this interface. authenticating - the peer is being authenticated if the dot1x mode is enabled. authorizing - the peer is being authorized. sapNegotiating - the SA(Security Association) is being negotiated with the peer. open - the line is up from TrustSec perspective. held - a hold down timer is set. disconnecting - a failure has occurred, or the TrustSec link is going down, or TrustSec is being disabled. invalid - unable to start the TrustSec state machine. licenseError - No MACSec software license.

ctsiIfConfigTable.name: ctsiIfConfigTable
ctsiIfConfigTable.description: A list of the TrustSec capable interfaces.

ctsiIfConfigEntry.name: ctsiIfConfigEntry
ctsiIfConfigEntry.description: An entry contains the configuration information for a particular TrustSec interface.

ctsiIfModeCapability.name: ctsiIfModeCapability
ctsiIfModeCapability.description: This object indicates the supported TrustSec mode on this interface.

ctsiIfConfiguredMode.name: ctsiIfConfiguredMode
ctsiIfConfiguredMode.description: This object indicates the TrustSec mode currently configured on the interface. Each mode may have a corresponding entry in its corresponding configuration table. unknown - The configured TrustSec mode is none of the following. none - TrustSec is not configured in any mode. dot1x - TrustSec dot1x mode is configured for this interface. TrustSec system will use 802.1x for authentication, RADIUS for authorization and SAP negotiation for SA parameter. manual - TrustSec manual mode is configured for this interface. The authentication was bypassed in manual mode. User needs to manually to configure the policy and the SAP negotiation parameter. l3Forward - TrustSec L3 forwarding mode is configured for this interface.

ctsiIfCacheClear.name: ctsiIfCacheClear
ctsiIfCacheClear.description: This object allows user to clear the cache for the specific TrustSec interface by setting the value to 'true'. Setting the value to 'false' has no effect. When read, this object always returns 'false'.

ctsiIfRekey.name: ctsiIfRekey
ctsiIfRekey.description: This object allows user to re-generate the SAP key for the specific TrustSec interface by setting the value to 'true'. Setting the value to 'false' has no effect. When read, this object always returns 'false'.

ctsiIfDot1xTable.name: ctsiIfDot1xTable
ctsiIfDot1xTable.description: A list of the interfaces which have TrustSec dot1x mode configuration information.

ctsiIfDot1xEntry.name: ctsiIfDot1xEntry
ctsiIfDot1xEntry.description: An entry containing the TrustSec dot1x configuration for a particular interface. An entry can be created or deleted by using ctsiIfDot1xRowStatus. An entry can only be created if the value of corresponding instance of ctsiIfConfiguredMode is 'none' and the 'dot1x' BIT of corresponding instance ctsiIfModeCapability is set.

ctsiIfDot1xSgtPropagateEnabled.name: ctsiIfDot1xSgtPropagateEnabled
ctsiIfDot1xSgtPropagateEnabled.description: This object specifies whether the SGT propagation is enabled on this interface.

ctsiIfDot1xReauthInterval.name: ctsiIfDot1xReauthInterval
ctsiIfDot1xReauthInterval.description: This object specifies the re-authentication interval applied to this interface when it is not provided from the ACS.

ctsiIfDot1xSapModeList.name: ctsiIfDot1xSapModeList
ctsiIfDot1xSapModeList.description: This object specifies the advertised modes for the SAP negotiation on this interface. Modes are executed in the order as specified in the mode list. Mode which is at the beginning of the method list will be executed first. Method which is at the end of mode list will be executed last. This object is not allowed to be set to a zero length string.

ctsiIfDot1xDownloadReauthInterval.name: ctsiIfDot1xDownloadReauthInterval
ctsiIfDot1xDownloadReauthInterval.description: This object indicates the re-authentication interval which is downloaded from ACS. A value of zero indicates no re-authentication interval is downloaded from ACS. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not applicable on this interface.

ctsiIfDot1xOperReauthInterval.name: ctsiIfDot1xOperReauthInterval
ctsiIfDot1xOperReauthInterval.description: This object indicates the operational re-authentication interval of the interface. A value of zero indicates that dot1x re-authentication is disabled on this interface. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not applicable on this interface.

ctsiIfDot1xReauthTimeLeft.name: ctsiIfDot1xReauthTimeLeft
ctsiIfDot1xReauthTimeLeft.description: This object indicates the leftover time of the current authentication session. A value of zero indicates the re-authentication is in progress. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not applicable on this interface.

ctsiIfDot1xStorageType.name: ctsiIfDot1xStorageType
ctsiIfDot1xStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row.

ctsiIfDot1xRowStatus.name: ctsiIfDot1xRowStatus
ctsiIfDot1xRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. All writable objects in this row may be modified at any time.

ctsiIfManualTable.name: ctsiIfManualTable
ctsiIfManualTable.description: A list of the interfaces which have TrustSec manual mode configuration information.

ctsiIfManualEntry.name: ctsiIfManualEntry
ctsiIfManualEntry.description: An entry containing the TrustSec manual configuration information for a particular interface. An entry can be created or deleted by using ctsiIfManualRowStatus. An entry can only be created if the value of corresponding instance of ctsiIfConfiguredMode is 'none' and the 'manual' BIT of corresponding instance ctsiIfModeCapability is set.

ctsiIfManualDynamicPeerId.name: ctsiIfManualDynamicPeerId
ctsiIfManualDynamicPeerId.description: This object specifies the peer's device identity which is used to obtain the desired policy for authorization request. Setting a none-zero value on this object is not allowed if the value of ctsiIfManualStaticSgt is not set to zero. A zero length string indicates that the policy acquisition from the ACS using the peer's identity is disabled on this interface.

ctsiIfManualStaticSgt.name: ctsiIfManualStaticSgt
ctsiIfManualStaticSgt.description: This object specifies the statically configured SGT for tagging the ingress traffic from the peer. Setting a none-zero value on this object is not allowed if the value of ctsiIfManualDynamicPeerId is not set to a zero length string. A value of zero indicates that no statically SGT tagging.

ctsiIfManualStaticSgtTrusted.name: ctsiIfManualStaticSgtTrusted
ctsiIfManualStaticSgtTrusted.description: This object specifies the peer's SGT assignment trust state. This object only can be set when ctsiIfManualStaticSgt is none-zero.

ctsiIfManualSgtPropagateEnabled.name: ctsiIfManualSgtPropagateEnabled
ctsiIfManualSgtPropagateEnabled.description: This object specifies whether the SGT propagation is enabled on this interface.

ctsiIfManualSapPmk.name: ctsiIfManualSapPmk
ctsiIfManualSapPmk.description: This object specifies the PMK used by SAP. A zero length string for this object indicates the SAP negotiation is disabled on this interface.

ctsiIfManualSapModeList.name: ctsiIfManualSapModeList
ctsiIfManualSapModeList.description: This object specified the advertised modes for the SAP negotiation on this interface. Modes are executed in the order as specified in the mode list. Mode which is at the beginning of the mode list will be executed first. Mode which is at the end of mode list will be executed last. Value of this object will becomes zero length octet if SAP negotiation is disabled. This object is not allowed to be set to a zero length string.

ctsiIfManualStorageType.name: ctsiIfManualStorageType
ctsiIfManualStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row.

ctsiIfManualRowStatus.name: ctsiIfManualRowStatus
ctsiIfManualRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. All writable objects in this row may be modified at any time.

ctsiIfL3ForwardTable.name: ctsiIfL3ForwardTable
ctsiIfL3ForwardTable.description: A list of the interfaces which have TrustSec L3 forwarding configuration information.

ctsiIfL3ForwardEntry.name: ctsiIfL3ForwardEntry
ctsiIfL3ForwardEntry.description: An entry containing the TrustSec L3 forwarding configuration information for a particular interface. An entry can be created or deleted by using ctsiIfL3ForwardRowStatus. An entry can only be created if the value of corresponding instance of ctsiIfConfiguredMode is 'none' and the 'l3Forward' BIT of corresponding instance ctsiIfModeCapability is set.

ctsiIfL3ForwardMode.name: ctsiIfL3ForwardMode
ctsiIfL3ForwardMode.description: This object specifies the type of L3 forwarding for the interface. l3Ipv4Forward - TrustSec L3 IPv4 forwarding. l3Ipv6Forward - TrustSec L3 IPv6 forwarding. l3IpForward - TrustSec L3 IPv6 and IPv4 forwarding.

ctsiIfL3ForwardStorageType.name: ctsiIfL3ForwardStorageType
ctsiIfL3ForwardStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row.

ctsiIfL3ForwardRowStatus.name: ctsiIfL3ForwardRowStatus
ctsiIfL3ForwardRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. All writable objects in this row may be modified at any time.

ctsiIfStatusTable.name: ctsiIfStatusTable
ctsiIfStatusTable.description: A list of TrustSec enabled interfaces.

ctsiIfStatusEntry.name: ctsiIfStatusEntry
ctsiIfStatusEntry.description: An entry contains the information of the specific TrustSec interface. A entry is created by system when TrustSec is enabled for an interface. An entry is deleted by system if TrustSec is disabled for an interface.

ctsiIfControllerState.name: ctsiIfControllerState
ctsiIfControllerState.description: This object indicates the current IFC state of this interface.

ctsiIfAuthenticationStatus.name: ctsiIfAuthenticationStatus
ctsiIfAuthenticationStatus.description: This object indicates the current TrustSec authentication status of this interface. unknown - status not covered by any of the follow enumerations. succeeded - authentication is succeeded. rejected - authentication is rejected. logOff - peer logged off. noRespond - peer no respond. notApplicable - bypassing the authentication. incomplete - authentication is not completed. failed - authentication failed.

ctsiIfPeerId.name: ctsiIfPeerId
ctsiIfPeerId.description: This object indicates the device identity or symbolic group name of the remote peer.

ctsiIfPeerAdvCapability.name: ctsiIfPeerAdvCapability
ctsiIfPeerAdvCapability.description: This object indicates the advertised capabilities of the remote peer associated with this interface.

ctsiIfAuthorizationStatus.name: ctsiIfAuthorizationStatus
ctsiIfAuthorizationStatus.description: This object indicates the current TrustSec authorization status of the interface. unknown - status not covered by any of the follow enumerations. inProgress - authorization in progress. succeeded - authorization succeeded. failed - authorization failed. fallBackPolicy - apply the fallback policy. incomplete - authorization aborted. peerSucceeded - apply the peer policy succeeded. rbaclSucceeded - apply the RBACL policy succeeded. policySucceeded - apply the all policy succeeded.

ctsiIfPeerSgt.name: ctsiIfPeerSgt
ctsiIfPeerSgt.description: This object indicates the SGT value of the remote peer.

ctsiIfPeerSgtTrusted.name: ctsiIfPeerSgtTrusted
ctsiIfPeerSgtTrusted.description: This object indicates whether the SGT of the remote peer is trusted.

ctsiIfSapNegotiationStatus.name: ctsiIfSapNegotiationStatus
ctsiIfSapNegotiationStatus.description: This object indicates the SAP negotiation status on this interface. notApplicable - SAP disabled on local or remote peer is not SAP capable. unknown - status not covered by any of the follow enumerations. inProgress - SAP negotiation in progress. succeeded - SAP negotiation completed. failed - SAP negotiation failed. licenseError - No MACSec software license.

ctsiIfSapNegModeList.name: ctsiIfSapNegModeList
ctsiIfSapNegModeList.description: This object indicates the operational SAP negotiation mode list on this interface.

ctsiIfCacheExpirationTime.name: ctsiIfCacheExpirationTime
ctsiIfCacheExpirationTime.description: This object indicates the time when the current cached data applied on the interface will be expired. A value of zero indicates that the cached data will never be expired.

ctsiIfCacheDataSource.name: ctsiIfCacheDataSource
ctsiIfCacheDataSource.description: This object indicates the source of cached data applied to the interface.

ctsiIfCriticalAuthStatus.name: ctsiIfCriticalAuthStatus
ctsiIfCriticalAuthStatus.description: This object indicates the CTS Critical-Auth status of interface. disable - link is not in Critical-Auth mode. cache - link is in Critical-Auth cached mode. default - link is in Critical-Auth default mode.

ctsiIfStatsTable.name: ctsiIfStatsTable
ctsiIfStatsTable.description: A list of Cisco Trusted Security capable interface.

ctsiIfStatsEntry.name: ctsiIfStatsEntry
ctsiIfStatsEntry.description: An entry contains the statistics information of a particular TrustSec interface. An entry created by system for each interface is TrustSec enabled. An entry deleted by system for each interface is TrustSec disabled.

ctsiIfAuthenticationSuccess.name: ctsiIfAuthenticationSuccess
ctsiIfAuthenticationSuccess.description: The number of times that peer has been successfully authenticated on this interface.

ctsiIfAuthenticationReject.name: ctsiIfAuthenticationReject
ctsiIfAuthenticationReject.description: The number of times that peer has been rejected in authentication on this interface.

ctsiIfAuthenticationFailure.name: ctsiIfAuthenticationFailure
ctsiIfAuthenticationFailure.description: The number of times that peer has been failed in authentication on this interface.

ctsiIfAuthenticationNoResponse.name: ctsiIfAuthenticationNoResponse
ctsiIfAuthenticationNoResponse.description: The number of times that no authentication respond received from the remote peer associated with this interface.

ctsiIfAuthenticationLogoff.name: ctsiIfAuthenticationLogoff
ctsiIfAuthenticationLogoff.description: The number of times that received authentication log off from the peer associated with this interface.

ctsiIfAuthorizationSuccess.name: ctsiIfAuthorizationSuccess
ctsiIfAuthorizationSuccess.description: The number of times that the peer entity successfully passed the TrustSec authorization challenge on this interface.

ctsiIfAuthorizationPolicyFail.name: ctsiIfAuthorizationPolicyFail
ctsiIfAuthorizationPolicyFail.description: The number of time that fail to access policy or refresh the policy for TrustSec authorization on this interface.

ctsiIfAuthorizationFail.name: ctsiIfAuthorizationFail
ctsiIfAuthorizationFail.description: The number of times that peer has been failed in TrustSec authorization on this interface.

ctsiIfSapSuccess.name: ctsiIfSapSuccess
ctsiIfSapSuccess.description: The number of times that SAP negotiation is succeed on this interface.

ctsiIfSapFail.name: ctsiIfSapFail
ctsiIfSapFail.description: The number of times that SAP negotiation has failed on this interface.

ctsiAuthorizationTable.name: ctsiAuthorizationTable
ctsiAuthorizationTable.description: A list of authorized remote peers on this device.

ctsiAuthorizationEntry.name: ctsiAuthorizationEntry
ctsiAuthorizationEntry.description: An entry containing the management information for a particular authorized peer. An entry is created when the policy acquired from the ACS for a new peer. An entry is deleted when the authorization of the peer has expired or fails to refresh its policy.

ctsiAuthorizationPeerId.name: ctsiAuthorizationPeerId
ctsiAuthorizationPeerId.description: This object indicates the device identity or symbolic group name of the remote peer.

ctsiAuthorizationPeerSgt.name: ctsiAuthorizationPeerSgt
ctsiAuthorizationPeerSgt.description: This object indicates the SGT of the remote peer.

ctsiAuthorizationState.name: ctsiAuthorizationState
ctsiAuthorizationState.description: This object indicates the current state of the authorization entity. unknown - none of the following states. start - authorization entity created and initialized. waitingRespond - a policy request has been made by remote peer to the ACS and waiting for the response. assessing - the policy been received from ACS and is being assessed. complete - policy has been received and assessed. failure - failed to download the policy from the ACS.

ctsiAuthorizationLastRefresh.name: ctsiAuthorizationLastRefresh
ctsiAuthorizationLastRefresh.description: The object indicates the date and time when the authorized peer was last refreshed.

ctsiAuthorizationTimeLeft.name: ctsiAuthorizationTimeLeft
ctsiAuthorizationTimeLeft.description: This object indicates the leftover time for the current policy. A value of zero indicates that policy refresh is in progress. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not applicable on this authorization entry.

ctsiAuthorizationTimeToRefresh.name: ctsiAuthorizationTimeToRefresh
ctsiAuthorizationTimeToRefresh.description: This object indicates the time left to start the policy refresh. A value of zero indicates that policy refresh is in progress. A value of -1 indicates that this object is not applicable on this authorization entry.

ctsiAuthorizationCacheDataSource.name: ctsiAuthorizationCacheDataSource
ctsiAuthorizationCacheDataSource.description: This object indicates the source of cached data.

ctsiAuthorizationStatus.name: ctsiAuthorizationStatus
ctsiAuthorizationStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this authorization peer. unknown - status not covered by any of the follow enumerations. inProgress - new authorization link created or add a new policy request for an existing link. succeeded - policy received successful. failed - policy download failed. fallbackPolicy - download policy failed apply fallback policy. incomplete - policy received incomplete.

ctsiIfcStatsTable.name: ctsiIfcStatsTable
ctsiIfcStatsTable.description: A list of IFC state statistic on this device.

ctsiIfcStatsEntry.name: ctsiIfcStatsEntry
ctsiIfcStatsEntry.description: An entry containing the total number of interfaces which are currently belong to a particular IFC state.

ctsiIfcState.name: ctsiIfcState
ctsiIfcState.description: This object indicates the IFC state.

ctsiIfcStatsIfCount.name: ctsiIfcStatsIfCount
ctsiIfcStatsIfCount.description: The total number of interfaces on the device which is currently in the IFC state.

ctsiAuthenticationSuccess.name: ctsiAuthenticationSuccess
ctsiAuthenticationSuccess.description: The total number of times that remote peers authentication succeed on this device.

ctsiAuthenticationReject.name: ctsiAuthenticationReject
ctsiAuthenticationReject.description: The total number of times that remote peers authentication rejected on this device.

ctsiAuthenticationFailure.name: ctsiAuthenticationFailure
ctsiAuthenticationFailure.description: The total number of times that remote peers authentication failed on this device

ctsiAuthenticationLogoff.name: ctsiAuthenticationLogoff
ctsiAuthenticationLogoff.description: The total number of times that remote peer log off on this device.

ctsiAuthenticationNoRespond.name: ctsiAuthenticationNoRespond
ctsiAuthenticationNoRespond.description: The total number of times that not received authentication respond from remote peer on this device.

ctsiAuthorizationSuccess.name: ctsiAuthorizationSuccess
ctsiAuthorizationSuccess.description: The total number of times that remote peer authorization succeed on this device.

ctsiAuthorizationFailure.name: ctsiAuthorizationFailure
ctsiAuthorizationFailure.description: The total number of times that remote peer TrustSec authorization failed on this device.

ctsiAuthorizationPolicyFailure.name: ctsiAuthorizationPolicyFailure
ctsiAuthorizationPolicyFailure.description: The number of time that fail to access policy or refresh the policy for TrustSec authorization on this device.

ctsiSapNegotiationSuccess.name: ctsiSapNegotiationSuccess
ctsiSapNegotiationSuccess.description: The total number of times that TrustSec SAP negotiation succeed on this device.

ctsiSapNegotiationFailure.name: ctsiSapNegotiationFailure
ctsiSapNegotiationFailure.description: The total number of times that TrustSec SAP negotiation failure on this device.

ctsiInDot1xModeIfCount.name: ctsiInDot1xModeIfCount
ctsiInDot1xModeIfCount.description: The total number of interfaces on the device which is in TrustSec 802.1X mode.

ctsiInManualModeIfCount.name: ctsiInManualModeIfCount
ctsiInManualModeIfCount.description: The total number of interfaces on the device which is in TrustSec Manual mode.

ctsiInL3ForwardModeIfCount.name: ctsiInL3ForwardModeIfCount
ctsiInL3ForwardModeIfCount.description: The total number of interfaces on the device which is in TrustSec Layer 3 forwarding mode.

ctsiAuthorizationFailNotifEnable.name: ctsiAuthorizationFailNotifEnable
ctsiAuthorizationFailNotifEnable.description: This object specifies whether the system generates the ctsiAuthorizationFailNotif. A value of 'false' will prevent ctsiAuthorizationFailNotif notifications from being generated by this system.

ctsiIfAddSupplicantFailNotifEnable.name: ctsiIfAddSupplicantFailNotifEnable
ctsiIfAddSupplicantFailNotifEnable.description: This object specifies whether the system generates the ctsiIfAddSupplicantFailNotif. A value of 'false' will prevent ctsiIfAddSupplicantFailNotif notifications from being generated by this system.

ctsiIfAuthenticationFailNotifEnable.name: ctsiIfAuthenticationFailNotifEnable
ctsiIfAuthenticationFailNotifEnable.description: This object specifies whether the system generates the ctsiIfAuthenticationFailNotif. A value of 'false' will prevent ctsiIfAuthenticationFailNotif notifications from being generated by this system.

ctsiIfSapNegotiationFailNotifEnable.name: ctsiIfSapNegotiationFailNotifEnable
ctsiIfSapNegotiationFailNotifEnable.description: This object specifies whether the system generates the ctsiIfSapNegotiationFailNotif. A value of 'false' will prevent ctsiIfSapNegotiationFailNotif notifications from being generated by this system.

ctsiIfUnauthorizedNotifEnable.name: ctsiIfUnauthorizedNotifEnable
ctsiIfUnauthorizedNotifEnable.description: This object specifies whether the system generates the ctsiIfUnauthorizedNotif. A value of 'false' will prevent ctsiIfUnauthorizedNotif notifications from being generated by this system.

ctsiIfNotifMessage.name: ctsiIfNotifMessage
ctsiIfNotifMessage.description: This object indicates detail message associated with notifications.

ctsiIfDot1xPaeRole.name: ctsiIfDot1xPaeRole
ctsiIfDot1xPaeRole.description: This object indicates dot1x PAE role information. notApplicable: Dot1x PAE role is not applicable in this notification. authenticator: PAE Authenticator. supplicant : PAE Supplicant.

ctsiAuthorizationFailNotif.name: ctsiAuthorizationFailNotif
ctsiAuthorizationFailNotif.description: A ctsiAuthorizationFailNotif is generated when the policy acquisition failed for the peer.

ctsiIfAddSupplicantFailNotif.name: ctsiIfAddSupplicantFailNotif
ctsiIfAddSupplicantFailNotif.description: A ctsiIfAddSupplicantFailNotif is generated when the system fails to add dot1x supplicant for an interface.

ctsiIfAuthenticationFailNotif.name: ctsiIfAuthenticationFailNotif
ctsiIfAuthenticationFailNotif.description: A ctsiIfAuthenticationFailNotif is generated when an authentication error for the peer is detected for an interface.

ctsiIfSapNegotiationFailNotif.name: ctsiIfSapNegotiationFailNotif
ctsiIfSapNegotiationFailNotif.description: A ctsiIfSapNegotiationFailNotif is generated when a SAP negotiation error with the peer is detected for an interface.

ctsiIfUnauthorizedNotif.name: ctsiIfUnauthorizedNotif
ctsiIfUnauthorizedNotif.description: A ctsiIfUnauthorizedNotif is generated when a interface becomes unauthorized on the Cisco TrustSec link.
